section.t:
The header field defined in this document is expected to serve several purposes:
Convey the results of various message authentication checks, which are applied by upstream filters and Mail Transfer Agents (MTAs) and then passed to MUAs and downstream filters within the same "trust domain". Such agents might wish to render those results to end users or to use those data to apply more or less stringent content checks based on authentication results;
Provide a common location within a message for this data;
Create an extensible framework for reporting new authentication methods as they emerge.

Result codes were also registered in other RFCs as follows:
Vouch By Reference (in , represented by "vbr");
Authorized Third-Party Signatures (in , represented by "dkim-atps");
Author Domain Signing Practices (in , represented by "dkim-adsp");
Require-Recipient-Valid-Since (in , represented by "rrvs");
S/MIME (in , represented by "smime").
The ability to report different DKIM results for a multiply-signed message (in ).

An entry in this registry contains the following:
the name of the method;
a reference to the document that created this entry, if any (see below);
a "ptype" value appropriate for use with that method;
a "property" value matching that "ptype" also appropriate for use with that method;
a brief description of the value to be supplied with that method/ptype/property tuple;
the status of this entry, which is either:
The entry is in current use.
The entry is no longer in current use.
a version number associated with the method (preferably starting at "1").

